condition.narrative: Specific target levels for the CRI and for controlling increases in operating costs have been agreed with the EDEs

baseline.value: Baseline varies according to each specific circuit, but the assessment should be done using the 2006 baseline. EdeNorte range:50-87 %, EdeSur constant at 62%, EdeEste 50-75%

comment.narrative: (ASAI) is the ratio of the total number of customer hours that service was available during a given time period to the totalcustomer hours demanded.

target.value: 87% for all three EDE's. It is unlikely they reach the targets by the closing date of the project.

comment.narrative: Data reported by CDEEE as June and July 2013. No more recent data available.

title.narrative: Average service availability index (ASAI) per circuits with project investments and in each EDE as whole

comment.narrative: 1st Quarter 2007 Baseline (SIE Indicadores Calidad del Servicio 2007). Numbers in percentage represent ASAI for EDE as a whole.(ASAI) is the ratio of the total number of customer hours that service was available during a given time period to the totalcustomer hours demanded.
Data based on CDEEE's trimester reporting as of June, 2013. New data for EdeSur and EdeNorte were not reported.
2007 baseline: audited TOC, and VE (CDEEE report on operational expenditures).

target.value: There is no target because the indicator was designed to show only the tendency of the operating costs.

comment.narrative: TOCi < TOCi-1xK(Audited Report on Operational Expenditures using formula).

actual.value: Total EDEs operating costs: US$226 millionEdeNorte: US$56 millionEdeEste: US$71 millionEdeSur: US$99 million

comment.narrative: Data reported by CDEEE as of September 2012. This data needs to be verified with the Annual Audited Report to be delivered inMarch2013 as well as with the ongoing independent audit

baseline.value: Baseline varies according to each specific circuit, but the assessment should be done using the 2007 baseline. EdeNorte range: 9%to 56% EdeSur range: 25% to 65% EdeEste range: 28% - 76%

comment.narrative: CRI formula = (energy billed by distribution companies / energy purchased by distribution companies) multiplied by (electricitybillings paid by consumers / total electricity billings issued to consumers).

target.value: The target value varies according to each specific circuit. For EdeNorte that target ranges between 64% to 75%. For EdeSur thetarget ranges from 34% to 84%. For EdeEste the target is fixed at 84%.

comment.narrative: Data based on CDEEE's monthly reporting as of July, 2013.

It was revealed that the three separate regions were regulated under different tariff structures and therefore required differentbaselines for the project monitoring indicators, therefore the project is using the adjusted Dec 2010 figures as a baseline.CRIformula = (energy billed by distribution companies / energy purchased by distribution companies) multiplied by (electricitybillings paid by consumers / total electricity billings issued to consumers).
Data used to calculate this indicator has been extracted from CDEEE monthly report of May 2013 (latest data available).
